1
00:00:00,530 --> 00:00:02,910
Hey, was that Ayumelo's...

2
00:00:02,910 --> 00:00:04,990
Yes. He delivers alcohol here.

3
00:00:04,990 --> 00:00:07,300
Oh, I had no idea.

4
00:00:07,300 --> 00:00:11,270
You know our regulars Sumi-chan
and Sekita-san? He's also their ex.

5
00:00:11,270 --> 00:00:12,410
He's exes with two people here?

6
00:00:12,410 --> 00:00:14,430
He isn't anyone suspicious, right?

7
00:00:14,430 --> 00:00:18,690
Two ex-girlfriends from the same bar
sounds suspicious to me.

8
00:00:18,690 --> 00:00:21,710
I guess. It might just be a coincidence, though.

9
00:00:21,710 --> 00:00:23,940
"A coincidence"? I hope so...

10
00:00:23,940 --> 00:00:25,850
This is so strong.

11
00:00:25,850 --> 00:00:27,580
Excuse me.

12
00:00:28,460 --> 00:00:31,730
Could I hear more about that, in detail?

13
00:00:33,510 --> 00:00:36,670
Is it true that Ayumi is dating a womanizer?

14
00:00:36,670 --> 00:00:39,540
- What?
- And you are?

15
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:41,140
Are you okay, Katsuo?

16
00:00:41,140 --> 00:00:44,000
"Katsuo"? Oh!

17
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:45,950
- Are you Ayumelo's...
- Yes.

18
00:00:45,950 --> 00:00:49,870
So please, tell me more about this womanizer.

19
00:00:49,870 --> 00:00:53,460
He's not exactly a womanizer,
but a few of his exes are regulars here.

20
00:00:53,460 --> 00:00:55,210
Several exes?

21
00:00:55,210 --> 00:00:56,810
No, just a few.

22
00:00:56,810 --> 00:00:58,550
Unbelievable... Several?

23
00:00:58,550 --> 00:01:00,450
Just a few, Sir.

24
00:01:01,230 --> 00:01:04,150
Sekita-san, Sumi-chan,
could you come here for a second?

25
00:01:04,150 --> 00:01:05,280
What's up?

26
00:01:05,280 --> 00:01:09,830
This man wants to know more about Minato-kun.

27
00:01:09,830 --> 00:01:11,680
What? "About Minato"?

28
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:14,550
These girls are both Minato-kun's exes.

29
00:01:14,550 --> 00:01:15,830
Really?

30
00:01:15,830 --> 00:01:18,480
So what sort of guy is Minato-kun?

31
00:01:20,390 --> 00:01:23,350
How should I describe him...

32
00:01:23,350 --> 00:01:26,100
He's kind and a good guy, but...

33
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:28,360
- "But"? But what?
- What can I say?

34
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:33,210
He's quick to start dating
and quick to break up, too.

35
00:01:33,210 --> 00:01:34,190
What?

36
00:01:34,190 --> 00:01:36,970
Look. That girl is another of his exes.

37
00:01:36,970 --> 00:01:39,930
That girl is, too.
They didn't even last a month, did they?

38
00:01:39,930 --> 00:01:41,620
No, she said they lasted a week.

39
00:01:41,620 --> 00:01:43,070
What?

40
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:45,190
In other words, he's...

41
00:01:45,190 --> 00:01:48,720
Let me guess... a mass consumption lover boy?

42
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:50,110
- Exactly!
- Is he really like that?

43
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:51,370
"Mass..."

44
00:01:51,370 --> 00:01:53,260
"consumption..."

45
00:01:53,260 --> 00:01:54,910
"lover boy"?

46
00:01:54,910 --> 00:01:57,040
Seriously?

47
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:04,880
Right, trash day.

48
00:02:13,010 --> 00:02:14,760
[Proper ways to dispose of trash]

49
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:16,860
"Mass consumption"...
[Mass consumption destroys our future!]

50
00:02:16,860 --> 00:02:18,600
I have a boyfriend now.

51
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:23,180
And I really, truly love him.

52
00:02:23,180 --> 00:02:25,970
This is quite risky, Ayumi.

53
00:02:25,970 --> 00:02:29,340
- I'm heading out now.
- Sure.

54
00:02:29,340 --> 00:02:32,570
Sorry to make you stay over
when you have an early day today.

55
00:02:32,570 --> 00:02:34,190
It's fine.

56
00:02:35,030 --> 00:02:37,640
I wanted to stay with you.

57
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,050
I'm happy to hear that.

58
00:02:48,770 --> 00:02:51,450
I wish we could spend more time together.

59
00:02:51,450 --> 00:02:53,880
Don't you wish we could spend more time together?

60
00:02:55,270 --> 00:03:01,050
You have early shifts, while I work late,
so we hardly get to see each other.

61
00:03:01,050 --> 00:03:03,320
I was just thinking the same thing.

62
00:03:06,670 --> 00:03:08,400
Say, Ayu-chan.

63
00:03:10,580 --> 00:03:13,580
So long as you don't mind...

64
00:03:13,580 --> 00:03:16,060
Is he going to suggest living together?

65
00:03:16,060 --> 00:03:18,320
You can visit whenever, okay?

66
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:22,200
Okay.

67
00:03:23,260 --> 00:03:26,030
Eureka! I just had a great idea.

68
00:03:26,030 --> 00:03:27,010
What?

69
00:03:27,010 --> 00:03:29,980
It'll increase the amount of time
we can spend together.

70
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:31,030
Let me hear it.

71
00:03:31,030 --> 00:03:33,910
It must be hard to visit here all the time, right?

72
00:03:33,910 --> 00:03:37,040
- Yes.
- So we should...

73
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:40,560
- Move in together?
- play this app together!

74
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:43,920
See? We can poke our pet seals even when apart.
[Squishy-Seal Sim]

75
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:48,130
Sounds fun.

76
00:03:48,130 --> 00:03:51,980
Regarding the ongoing next-generation
toilet development project,

77
00:03:51,980 --> 00:03:54,870
we got 98% user satisfaction in user testing.

78
00:03:54,870 --> 00:03:56,460
It also received high praise at the exhibition,

79
00:03:56,460 --> 00:03:59,880
and many corporations
have already reached out to us.

80
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:02,290
I'd say our prototype is about perfect.

81
00:04:02,290 --> 00:04:05,350
Wow, great!

82
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,080
- Ebihara-kun.
- Yes, Sir?

83
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:11,610
What are your thoughts on sustainability?

84
00:04:11,610 --> 00:04:15,750
From now on, we must take into account
the issue of mass production.

85
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:17,150
"Mass production."

86
00:04:17,150 --> 00:04:19,700
I have a boyfriend now.

87
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:24,730
A key issue is how to
reduce mass consumption of water.

88
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:27,590
"Mass consumption"...

89
00:04:27,590 --> 00:04:31,300
Quick to start dating and quick to break up, too.

90
00:04:32,950 --> 00:04:35,370
Ayumi is being duped. I know it.

91
00:04:35,370 --> 00:04:40,180
She would never fall for such a player.

92
00:04:40,180 --> 00:04:44,610
Ayumi doesn't deserve to be "consumed"

93
00:04:44,610 --> 00:04:48,010
by men who indulge in such flings!

94
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:50,390
- Ebihara-kun?
- Absolutely not!

95
00:04:51,220 --> 00:04:56,820
I am against mass consumption
with every fiber of my being.

96
00:04:58,490 --> 00:05:00,480
Right, I agree wholeheartedly.

97
00:05:03,780 --> 00:05:08,210
[Could we talk?]

98
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:13,740
Katsuo-san, you wouldn't understand.

99
00:05:13,740 --> 00:05:16,010
Nor will I hope you'll attempt to.

100
00:05:19,350 --> 00:05:23,200
Mass production, mass consumption...

101
00:05:26,670 --> 00:05:28,990
He's agonizing over her.

102
00:05:28,990 --> 00:05:31,550
He sure is.

103
00:05:31,550 --> 00:05:33,740
What can I do?

104
00:05:36,090 --> 00:05:38,310
Ebihara's a role model.

105
00:05:38,310 --> 00:05:39,440
- Oh?
- What?

106
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:43,020
Who knew he was so passionate
about sustainability.

107
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:45,530
- Well...
- Darn it!

108
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:54,480
I won't let you tackle this issue alone.

109
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:56,990
Let's fight for what's right together!

110
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:01,660
We got this!

111
00:06:05,410 --> 00:06:08,680
Ebihara-san, are you all right?

112
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:11,770
You certainly look troubled.

113
00:06:12,770 --> 00:06:14,930
Listen.

114
00:06:16,010 --> 00:06:20,070
Ayumi... may be in danger.

115
00:06:20,770 --> 00:06:22,210
What?

116
00:06:22,210 --> 00:06:27,250
I see your point. Having several exes at one bar

117
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:29,520
- does seem a bit suspicious.
- Right?

118
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:33,740
Maybe he's just a nice guy who gets women,

119
00:06:33,740 --> 00:06:35,830
unlike you, Senpai.

120
00:06:37,130 --> 00:06:39,830
I understand why you'd worry, though.

121
00:06:39,830 --> 00:06:45,560
Listen, the Ayumi I know
would never fall for a guy like that.

122
00:06:46,230 --> 00:06:48,260
She's a kind, sweet girl.

123
00:06:48,260 --> 00:06:52,260
She's bright, cute, and has standards.

124
00:06:52,260 --> 00:06:54,420
- She has a cute smile, a cute demeanor, and—
- Okay, got it—

125
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:58,770
And she's adorable with her fair skin.

126
00:06:58,770 --> 00:07:03,200
However, Ebihara-san, maybe she wasn't her true self

127
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:07,050
when she was in a relationship with you.

128
00:07:07,050 --> 00:07:09,820
When I was in a relationship with you,

129
00:07:09,820 --> 00:07:13,880
I turned a blind eye to my own feelings.

130
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:16,160
That's impossible, probably.

131
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:20,690
Like I said, it's best to date casually
without the pressure of commitment.

132
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:23,960
That way, you won't fixate
on emotions or obsessions.

133
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:25,710
Hey, listen.

134
00:07:27,390 --> 00:07:29,520
Doesn't that become lonely?

135
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:30,610
Pardon?

136
00:07:30,610 --> 00:07:35,500
I said, "Doesn't that make you lonely?"

137
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:39,070
- Not at all.
- Really now.

138
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:42,120
But dealing with his ex-girlfriend

139
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:44,090
can be complicated, right?

140
00:07:44,090 --> 00:07:45,610
Did you call her my ex?

141
00:07:45,610 --> 00:07:48,090
Oh, come on, at least accept that as a fact.

142
00:07:48,090 --> 00:07:51,300
In any case, there's nothing you can do.
You're a stranger to her now.

143
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:53,100
She is your ex, anyway.

144
00:07:53,100 --> 00:07:56,300
- Then if you'll excuse me.
- What?

145
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:05,210
Am I really only a stranger now?

146
00:08:14,410 --> 00:08:17,630
You seem to be in a good mood, Yamagishi-san.
[Keep things organized]

147
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:19,160
Oh, well...

148
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,360
Maybe I am.

149
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:27,330
Things must be going well
with that high-spec boyfriend of yours.

150
00:08:27,330 --> 00:08:30,800
Oh, him? We broke up.

151
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,360
- What?
- It was recent, though.

152
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:35,620
- You two broke up?
- Yes.

153
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:40,250
- What an absolute waste!
- Sorry?

154
00:08:40,250 --> 00:08:43,230
I mean, you two dated since college, right?

155
00:08:43,230 --> 00:08:46,610
Not to mention he was loyal,
handsome, had a great-paying job,

156
00:08:46,610 --> 00:08:49,920
was set for success,
the third son from a good family.

157
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:51,740
Did I tell you that much?

158
00:08:51,740 --> 00:08:53,540
Half of that is my guess.

159
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:58,610
But you broke up with a man of his caliber?

160
00:08:58,610 --> 00:09:01,200
I certainly wouldn't be humming a jaunty tune.

161
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:03,200
I wouldn't even be breathing through my nose.

162
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:06,930
I found something I wanted to prioritize
over mere "conditions."

163
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:11,730
So that's the kind of person
you are, Yamagishi-san.

164
00:09:11,730 --> 00:09:13,460
What do you mean by "that kind of person"?

165
00:09:13,460 --> 00:09:16,540
The type who dares to go down dangerous paths.

166
00:09:17,630 --> 00:09:18,630
[Danger ahead!]

167
00:09:19,530 --> 00:09:21,020
Mari, follow me.

168
00:09:21,020 --> 00:09:22,930
This way.

169
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,280
A cliff...

170
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:27,210
I guess it's a dead end.

171
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:37,790
Mari! That man is no good for you.

172
00:09:37,790 --> 00:09:39,800
He's dangerous. Come back this way!

173
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:41,370
Don't come any closer!

174
00:09:41,370 --> 00:09:44,480
You're a stranger to me now!

175
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:46,070
Why?

176
00:09:46,070 --> 00:09:48,380
Mari, I... I always...

177
00:09:48,380 --> 00:09:51,700
Teruo, please give up on her!

178
00:09:51,700 --> 00:09:55,010
You no longer reside in Mari's heart!

179
00:09:55,010 --> 00:09:56,530
True, you don't.

180
00:09:56,530 --> 00:09:59,020
Damn it all!

181
00:09:59,020 --> 00:10:00,950
I won't give up on you, Mari.

182
00:10:00,950 --> 00:10:03,680
You will always be mine!

183
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:11,570
Teruo!

184
00:10:11,570 --> 00:10:15,640
Shunpy, thank you for protecting me.

185
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:18,310
- I never thought I'd be emotionally invested in Teruo's story.
- Mari.

186
00:10:18,310 --> 00:10:21,810
From now on, I want
all your relationships to be with me.

187
00:10:21,810 --> 00:10:26,650
We'll layer our feelings together,
like a relationship mille-feuille.

188
00:10:26,650 --> 00:10:32,800
I wish to share my feelings only with you.

189
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,260
Mari...

190
00:10:34,260 --> 00:10:38,980
Teruo, my condolences.

191
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:40,490
That was delicious.

192
00:10:40,490 --> 00:10:43,220
I'm actually a big fan of family restaurants.

193
00:10:43,220 --> 00:10:44,340
Really?

194
00:10:44,340 --> 00:10:48,290
Yes. Eating out means no dishes to clean too.

195
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:50,110
Fair point.

196
00:10:50,110 --> 00:10:54,720
- Yikes, I have to get going.
- No...

197
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,670
Having a later shift sounds rough.

198
00:10:56,670 --> 00:11:00,340
- Yes, I have many night shifts this week.
- Oh, really?

199
00:11:00,340 --> 00:11:04,090
If only we could eat out every day like this.

200
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:10,270
Personally, I wouldn't mind
cooking for you every day.

201
00:11:10,270 --> 00:11:13,130
I couldn't ask you to do that for me.

202
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:15,770
But if we lived together...

203
00:11:17,390 --> 00:11:19,280
I let it slip.

204
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:21,280
Should we?

205
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:22,480
What?

206
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:24,250
Should we move in together,

207
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:25,960
if you're okay with my place?

208
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:28,080
Wait, you wouldn't mind?

209
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:31,350
- No.
- Really?

210
00:11:31,350 --> 00:11:33,950
But think about it.

211
00:11:33,950 --> 00:11:37,150
We'd be together all the time. We'd be cohabiting.

212
00:11:37,150 --> 00:11:40,470
- Yes.
- Cohabiting means living together.

213
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:42,830
- You're okay with that?
- What?

214
00:11:42,830 --> 00:11:45,510
- Are you not?
- No, I am.

215
00:11:46,690 --> 00:11:49,400
Thank you. I'm glad you're okay with it.

216
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:50,950
Same here.

217
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:55,050
♫ I can change, trust me ♫

218
00:11:55,050 --> 00:11:57,050
Score!

219
00:11:57,960 --> 00:12:01,070
I managed to roll a Gold Squishy-Seal.

220
00:12:01,070 --> 00:12:03,960
I've been chasing after this seal forever.

221
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:06,610
Best day ever!

222
00:12:08,490 --> 00:12:10,220
"Best day ever."

223
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,600
Big news.

224
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:17,380
My ex-boyfriend and I are getting back together.

225
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:24,210
- Congratulations.
- Where's your gusto, my heartbreak buddy?

226
00:12:24,210 --> 00:12:28,350
Well, former heartbreak buddy, I guess.

227
00:12:28,350 --> 00:12:31,070
Come on, be happy for me.

228
00:12:31,070 --> 00:12:35,040
Sorry, but I really can't right now.

229
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:37,050
No, don't tell me...

230
00:12:37,050 --> 00:12:40,060
- Did you fall for me at some point?
- No.

231
00:12:40,060 --> 00:12:42,020
Not at all.

232
00:12:45,090 --> 00:12:48,720
Still worried about your ex?

233
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:53,890
Is there really nothing I can do for her now?

234
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:57,010
- No.
- No, right?

235
00:12:57,010 --> 00:12:58,920
But, see...

236
00:12:58,920 --> 00:13:01,780
If Ayumi continues this relationship,
she may end up unhappy.

237
00:13:01,780 --> 00:13:03,570
Should I really sit and do nothing?

238
00:13:03,570 --> 00:13:08,260
Ultimately, that is Ayumi-san's choice.

239
00:13:08,260 --> 00:13:12,350
You should focus on your own happiness, Katsuo.

240
00:13:12,350 --> 00:13:15,820
- Gosh, my own happiness?
- Yes.

241
00:13:15,820 --> 00:13:20,370
Isn't there anything you can obsess over
that's not your ex?

242
00:13:20,370 --> 00:13:21,740
- "Obsess over"?
- Yes.

243
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:23,970
- Like a hobby.
- "A hobby."

244
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:27,650
- Or, you know...
- Oh, I don't know.

245
00:13:27,650 --> 00:13:29,510
Does making dashi count?

246
00:13:29,510 --> 00:13:31,500
Sure, that's a great start.

247
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:38,980
Invest your time in a hobby, like making dashi.

248
00:13:38,980 --> 00:13:43,990
And before you know it,
you'll think back on her less and less.

249
00:13:54,250 --> 00:13:55,810
Okay.

250
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:08,000
That's the good one.

251
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,200
As time passes on...
[Dashi Pot | ¥2,475 ]

252
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,000
Maybe I'll get one of these.

253
00:14:13,940 --> 00:14:15,210
[Dried Sardines]

254
00:14:16,940 --> 00:14:19,920
Will my feelings for Ayumi truly wane?

255
00:14:22,620 --> 00:14:23,610
[Recipe of the month]

256
00:14:23,610 --> 00:14:25,970
Maybe...

257
00:14:25,970 --> 00:14:27,320
[Easy Chikuzenni for Beginners!]

258
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:32,400
Maybe I'm terrified
of getting used to life without Ayumi.

259
00:14:35,670 --> 00:14:36,990
Okay.

260
00:14:36,990 --> 00:14:38,970
Well...

261
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:45,530
- Aren't you rushing into this?
- What?

262
00:14:45,530 --> 00:14:47,230
You only just started dating him.

263
00:14:47,230 --> 00:14:50,980
Nagisa, you let me stay here
right after we met, right?

264
00:14:50,980 --> 00:14:54,320
Moving in together isn't the same as freeloading.

265
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:57,340
And I'll be sad to see you go.

266
00:14:57,340 --> 00:14:59,800
I'm sad about leaving, too.

267
00:15:00,630 --> 00:15:04,570
But I want to move in early,

268
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:09,440
to see if marriage is in the cards or not.

269
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:12,400
If that's what you want to do,
then I can't stop you.

270
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:15,100
Yes, it is what I want.

271
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:18,160
Because I decided
I wasn't going to endure anymore.

272
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:19,690
Right.

273
00:15:19,690 --> 00:15:21,630
Besides,

274
00:15:22,580 --> 00:15:27,200
I can't take advantage of
your and Taihei-kun's goodwill forever.

275
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,560
We really don't mind your company, though.

276
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:32,670
Still, I want to take this step for myself.

277
00:15:32,670 --> 00:15:35,310
- I see.
- Yes.

278
00:15:35,310 --> 00:15:40,670
Just know if anything happens,
you're welcome back any time, okay?

279
00:15:40,670 --> 00:15:42,380
Okay.

280
00:15:42,380 --> 00:15:44,930
- Thank you, Nagisa.
- Sure.

281
00:15:44,930 --> 00:15:47,960
- Say, why not bring that outfit with you?
- What?

282
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:49,390
Which outfit?

283
00:15:49,390 --> 00:15:51,400
Your "first date" outfit.

284
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:53,080
Thanks.

285
00:16:09,770 --> 00:16:11,200
Welcome.

286
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:13,310
Thanks for having me.

287
00:16:13,310 --> 00:16:15,570
The pleasure's mine.

288
00:16:15,570 --> 00:16:17,600
Come on in.

289
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:20,600
Thank you.

290
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:23,090
- Is that heavy?
- No.

291
00:16:23,860 --> 00:16:28,330
[Then You Try Making It!]

292
00:16:28,330 --> 00:16:31,000
