Bon appétit.
♫ The invisible colors must be yourself ♫

442
00:27:27,380 --> 00:27:33,200
♫ The invisible colors must be yourself ♫

443
00:27:40,710 --> 00:27:43,580
Even if I had a time machine to relive it all...

444
00:27:45,980 --> 00:27:49,140
I wouldn't know how far back I'd need to go.

445
00:27:55,750 --> 00:27:57,640
That's good.

446
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:19,550
Welcome back.

447
00:28:19,550 --> 00:28:23,320
Oh, Ayu-chan? You're still awake?

448
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:25,650
Yes, kind of.

449
00:28:26,730 --> 00:28:28,460
Is that...
[Minato-san]

450
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:32,530
I thought you might come back hungry.

451
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:35,230
Ayumi...

452
00:28:35,230 --> 00:28:38,840
Ayu-chan, your thoughtfulness makes me so happy.

453
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:45,890
I'm full now, but I promise I'll eat it tomorrow.

454
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:48,040
Okay, thank you.

455
00:28:52,060 --> 00:28:53,220
Gosh!

456
00:28:53,220 --> 00:28:56,080
You're working on a weekend, too?

457
00:28:56,080 --> 00:28:58,450
Hey, Minamikawa.

458
00:28:58,450 --> 00:28:59,970
And I thought I'd be alone.

459
00:28:59,970 --> 00:29:01,400
So did I.

460
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,630
Why did you come today?

461
00:29:02,630 --> 00:29:07,580
The chief told me to review our plans
for sustainability.

462
00:29:07,580 --> 00:29:09,850
I must rewrite everything from the ground up.

463
00:29:09,850 --> 00:29:12,070
Sounds like tough work.

464
00:29:12,070 --> 00:29:14,340
This is all your fault, Ebihara-san!

465
00:29:14,340 --> 00:29:15,390
Mine?

466
00:29:15,390 --> 00:29:18,800
Yes, you sparked the chief's motivation.

467
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:21,350
- I did?
- Yes.

468
00:29:29,380 --> 00:29:32,540
It's easier to concentrate
in the office, isn't it?

469
00:29:32,540 --> 00:29:34,360
Yes.

470
00:29:35,550 --> 00:29:37,880
Far easier than at home.

471
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:40,670
Being here keeps my mind off unnecessary things.

472
00:29:42,030 --> 00:29:45,510
Do you end up thinking about Ayumi-san
when you're at home?

473
00:29:46,590 --> 00:29:47,780
Something like that.

474
00:29:47,780 --> 00:29:51,020
Ebihara-san, if you were duct tape,
you'd be the really sticky type,

475
00:29:51,020 --> 00:29:53,720
like the kind you can't ever remove.

476
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:57,650
And would you be the removable, reusable kind?

477
00:29:57,650 --> 00:30:01,990
That's right. I could be reused
as many times as needed.

478
00:30:01,990 --> 00:30:06,560
To be fair, strong tape is useful.

479
00:30:12,220 --> 00:30:18,520
Sir, do you recall asking me
if I'd feel lonely without fixations?

480
00:30:19,680 --> 00:30:21,280
Did I say that?

481
00:30:21,280 --> 00:30:22,840
You did.

482
00:30:22,840 --> 00:30:24,950
Did I?

483
00:30:24,950 --> 00:30:27,230
You did, and it irritated me.

484
00:30:27,230 --> 00:30:28,550
What?

485
00:30:28,550 --> 00:30:33,840
Because... I couldn't entirely deny your point.

486
00:30:35,250 --> 00:30:39,620
Want to have roasted giblets
before we meet up next week?

487
00:30:39,620 --> 00:30:42,930
Sorry, I got myself a girlfriend.

488
00:30:45,310 --> 00:30:46,780
What?

489
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:49,340
So we can't meet anymore.

490
00:30:51,810 --> 00:30:55,890
I thought pragmatic relationships
were the way to go.

491
00:30:55,890 --> 00:31:03,540
But I'm not sure if the way I'm doing things
is truly making me happy.

492
00:31:09,900 --> 00:31:12,560
I also made shallow assumptions.

493
00:31:14,420 --> 00:31:18,500
Dating many people doesn't mean

494
00:31:18,500 --> 00:31:22,210
someone is making light of a relationship, right?

495
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:30,400
I'm done!

496
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:32,390
Great work.

497
00:31:32,390 --> 00:31:34,650
What about you, Ebihara-san? Almost done?

498
00:31:34,650 --> 00:31:37,600
Yes, just about.

499
00:31:40,110 --> 00:31:43,010
Then shall we grab a drink together?

500
00:31:49,190 --> 00:31:52,220
You're inviting me out to grab a drink.

501
00:31:52,220 --> 00:31:54,100
What's so wrong about that?

502
00:31:54,100 --> 00:31:55,940
Nothing. I'm just happy.

503
00:31:57,720 --> 00:32:00,580
It's nice to be invited out by a junior.

504
00:32:01,370 --> 00:32:04,830
Maybe you've become a senpai worth inviting out.

505
00:32:05,510 --> 00:32:06,640
You think so?

506
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:08,420
Who knows?

507
00:32:08,420 --> 00:32:09,540
Oh, all right.

508
00:32:09,540 --> 00:32:13,900
Oh, actually, I have a place I want to go,
if you'll join me.

509
00:32:15,980 --> 00:32:19,310
Why are we going to get some tequila?

510
00:32:19,310 --> 00:32:20,740
Ayumi was drinking it.

511
00:32:20,740 --> 00:32:24,910
- Still hung up on her?
- No, I'm trying to move on.

512
00:32:25,830 --> 00:32:30,740
But she really enjoyed herself while drinking the stuff.

513
00:32:30,740 --> 00:32:33,370
I just want to understand aspects of her

514
00:32:33,370 --> 00:32:35,150
I never bothered to learn, before I let go.

515
00:32:35,150 --> 00:32:37,590
[Mitsuya | Liquor Store]

516
00:32:37,590 --> 00:32:40,930
[We have local sake.]
