517
00:32:40,930 --> 00:32:42,530
Let's head in.

518
00:32:44,570 --> 00:32:48,410
- Wow, there's such a variety here.
- You're right.

519
00:32:48,410 --> 00:32:51,780
There are so many; I don't know which to choose.

520
00:32:52,990 --> 00:32:54,380
Welcome.

521
00:32:54,380 --> 00:32:56,220
Excuse me, where can we find some tequila?

522
00:32:56,220 --> 00:32:57,950
"Tequila"? Right this way, Sir.

523
00:32:57,950 --> 00:32:59,890
- I see.
- Here?

524
00:32:59,890 --> 00:33:02,300
This is all tequila?

525
00:33:02,300 --> 00:33:04,780
Tastings are available if you find one you like.

526
00:33:04,780 --> 00:33:06,950
Thank you.

527
00:33:10,610 --> 00:33:12,170
Wait a second...

528
00:33:15,060 --> 00:33:16,700
Are you Ayumi's...

529
00:33:18,380 --> 00:33:20,390
Is this Ayumi-san's boyfriend?

530
00:33:20,390 --> 00:33:23,670
Are you two Ayu-chan's friends?

531
00:33:23,670 --> 00:33:24,820
"Ayu-chan"?

532
00:33:24,820 --> 00:33:29,040
Oh, well, he's not exactly a friend, rather...

533
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:32,060
Could you be her ex?

534
00:33:34,130 --> 00:33:36,900
- Yes, I'm her ex.
- Now, now...

535
00:33:36,900 --> 00:33:40,080
It's nice to meet you. My name is Minato.

536
00:33:40,080 --> 00:33:42,160
I'm Katsuo.

537
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:44,140
Here, my treat.
[Tequila]

538
00:33:44,140 --> 00:33:46,170
- What, really?
- No, I'll pay.

539
00:33:46,170 --> 00:33:47,760
- Sir, why?
- I insist.

540
00:33:47,760 --> 00:33:49,500
Let's just accept his offer, Senpai.

541
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:52,730
This one is quite strong,
so don't overexert yourselves.

542
00:33:52,730 --> 00:33:55,120
Only sip it if you feel able to.

543
00:33:55,120 --> 00:33:56,570
If I feel "able to"?

544
00:33:56,570 --> 00:33:59,400
This guy's testing me.

545
00:33:59,400 --> 00:34:03,300
Don't force yourself to down the shot;
I have weaker tequila's as well.

546
00:34:03,300 --> 00:34:06,260
- I can down this shot, easily.
- Okay.

547
00:34:06,260 --> 00:34:07,880
Here you go.

548
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:10,670
- Thank you.
- Thanks, and cheers!

549
00:34:17,070 --> 00:34:18,630
- That's good!
- Right?

550
00:34:18,630 --> 00:34:21,740
It's rich. And what a complex scent.

551
00:34:21,740 --> 00:34:25,420
I always assumed
tequila was just a "frivolous drink,"

552
00:34:25,420 --> 00:34:27,300
but it's more than that.

553
00:34:27,300 --> 00:34:29,770
Now, where have I heard that before?

554
00:34:29,770 --> 00:34:31,900
Here we go!

555
00:34:31,900 --> 00:34:34,240
So...

556
00:34:35,910 --> 00:34:37,920
Minato-kun.

557
00:34:40,550 --> 00:34:45,000
You and Ayumi are...

558
00:34:46,970 --> 00:34:50,220
No, this is nothing for me to ask.

559
00:34:50,220 --> 00:34:52,260
We're dating each other.

560
00:34:52,260 --> 00:34:55,020
She recently moved into my place too.

561
00:34:55,020 --> 00:34:57,910
I love Ayu-chan a lot.

562
00:34:59,370 --> 00:35:01,590
- You hit where it hurts.
- What?

563
00:35:01,590 --> 00:35:04,230
But I spoke only the truth.

564
00:35:04,230 --> 00:35:06,610
- Sorry.
- That's no better.

565
00:35:06,610 --> 00:35:09,800
- Really?
- No, I'm fine.

566
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:12,010
It's the truth, after all.

567
00:35:12,010 --> 00:35:14,400
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

568
00:35:19,050 --> 00:35:20,480
- This is good.
- It really is.

569
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:21,700
Don't drink too much, Sir.

570
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:23,380
Me? I'm totally fine.

571
00:35:23,380 --> 00:35:24,850
You should join us, Minato-san.

572
00:35:24,850 --> 00:35:26,580
Sorry, I still have deliveries to make later.

573
00:35:26,580 --> 00:35:29,160
- I see.
- Here you go.

574
00:35:29,160 --> 00:35:33,280
I know this is easy to drink,
but it is quite strong. Don't overdo it.

575
00:35:33,280 --> 00:35:34,730
This much is nothing.

576
00:35:34,730 --> 00:35:37,600
Alcohol content isn't anything I worry about.

577
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:39,510
- Thank you, come again!
- It's really good.

578
00:35:39,510 --> 00:35:41,920
- This tequila is seriously good.
- Please, enjoy yourselves.

579
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:43,210
Thank you.

580
00:35:43,210 --> 00:35:46,800
If I'm being honest,
I'm not really a fan of this stuff.

581
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:49,730
But you're practically downing the bottle.

582
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:06,840
Would you like to share a snack?

583
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:08,160
It's poor weather for grabbing food, so...

584
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:10,830
- That looks delicious!
- It's a tortilla.

585
00:36:10,830 --> 00:36:12,840
- "A tortilla"?
- Wow...

586
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:14,780
- Let me try a bite.
- Go ahead.

587
00:36:14,780 --> 00:36:17,410
- And for you.
- Thank you.

588
00:36:17,410 --> 00:36:18,700
That's delicious.

589
00:36:18,700 --> 00:36:20,770
I didn't realize you could cook, Minato-san.

590
00:36:20,770 --> 00:36:23,140
I can only whip up simple dishes.

591
00:36:23,140 --> 00:36:25,780
Ayu-chan taught me this one.

592
00:36:26,530 --> 00:36:28,710
Must you keep hitting him where it hurts?

593
00:36:28,710 --> 00:36:30,550
That too?

594
00:36:30,550 --> 00:36:32,530
Sorry.

595
00:36:32,530 --> 00:36:36,190
I'm fine. You're speaking only the truth.

596
00:36:36,190 --> 00:36:40,740
This tortilla tastes better with company though,

597
00:36:40,740 --> 00:36:43,420
so I'm glad to have you both around.

598
00:36:43,420 --> 00:36:46,340
It really is delicious.

599
00:36:46,340 --> 00:36:47,960
All right!

600
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:49,200
Sir, aren't you drinking a bit too much?

601
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:51,690
I'm just getting started!

602
00:36:51,690 --> 00:36:55,100
- Ready?
- Oh, that's good!

603
00:36:59,830 --> 00:37:05,560
I wonder if Ayumi always preferred
guys like him instead.

604
00:37:05,560 --> 00:37:07,760
A cute guy,

605
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:10,030
the exact opposite of myself.

606
00:37:10,030 --> 00:37:12,220
You're cute, Katsuo-san.

607
00:37:12,220 --> 00:37:14,580
- What? How?
- Oh?

608
00:37:14,580 --> 00:37:18,400
It's cute how you're doing your best
to drink this tequila.

609
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:21,130
You've stabbed so deep,
you may have pierced him completely.

610
00:37:21,130 --> 00:37:22,920
No, I didn't stab him.

611
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:24,470
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

612
00:37:24,470 --> 00:37:26,450
We're looking for a wine to give as a gift.

613
00:37:26,450 --> 00:37:27,760
- Wine, is it?
- Yes.

614
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:30,170
- We keep our wine over here.
- Okay.

615
00:37:30,170 --> 00:37:32,350
- Sorry, may I pass behind you?
- Sure.

616
00:37:32,350 --> 00:37:34,490
- Right this way.
- Sure.

617
00:37:36,430 --> 00:37:38,040
How about a bottle like this?

618
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:39,530
- I like the label. It's cute.
- Right?

619
00:37:39,530 --> 00:37:40,770
- Isn't it?
- Yes, it's cute!

620
00:37:40,770 --> 00:37:45,960
That's what makes this bottle a great gift.

621
00:37:48,510 --> 00:37:50,320
Maybe, right now...

622
00:37:52,030 --> 00:37:57,920
Ayumi... is at her happiest.

623
00:37:57,920 --> 00:38:04,270
I have another suggestion right over here.

624
00:38:09,250 --> 00:38:11,350
Are you holding up, Sir?

625
00:38:12,630 --> 00:38:14,330
All your selections were wonderful.

626
00:38:14,330 --> 00:38:17,800
- We'll come get them all in the future.
- No problem.

627
00:38:18,930 --> 00:38:21,370
Senpai? Are you crying?

628
00:38:21,370 --> 00:38:22,980
- No.
- Are you all right?

629
00:38:22,980 --> 00:38:24,130
See? You stabbed right through him.

630
00:38:24,130 --> 00:38:26,950
- I really didn't mean to.
- No, I am not crying.

631
00:38:26,950 --> 00:38:28,730
- Minato-kun.
- Yes.

632
00:38:32,260 --> 00:38:34,170
Minato-kun.

633
00:38:34,170 --> 00:38:35,730
Yes.

634
00:38:40,700 --> 00:38:42,500
I leave Ayumi...

635
00:38:49,040 --> 00:38:50,950
in your caring hands.

636
00:38:57,320 --> 00:39:01,870
And I want you to really savor Ayumi's cooking.

637
00:39:01,870 --> 00:39:06,470
Her cooking is delicious,
so I want you to savor it well.

638
00:39:06,470 --> 00:39:10,670
- I will.
- And get plant-based dish soap, all right?

639
00:39:10,670 --> 00:39:14,650
She says the cheap stuff works,
but it makes her hands dry.

640
00:39:14,650 --> 00:39:18,720
And always buy two-ply toilet paper.

641
00:39:18,720 --> 00:39:24,530
Ayumi will say one-ply is fine,
but she prefers two-ply.

642
00:39:24,530 --> 00:39:28,880
- Noted.
- And get her good ice cream from time to time,

643
00:39:28,880 --> 00:39:34,940
not the lactose-free ice cream
or ice milk. Ice "cream."

644
00:39:34,940 --> 00:39:36,280
Okay.

645
00:39:37,190 --> 00:39:39,280
And one last thing.

646
00:39:53,570 --> 00:39:56,260
I want you to do what I couldn't for Ayumi.

647
00:39:58,310 --> 00:40:00,210
What I never did for her.

648
00:40:01,720 --> 00:40:04,100
What I never thought to do for her.

649
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:09,460
Please do many of those things for her.

650
00:40:13,300 --> 00:40:15,710
I leave Ayumi to you.

651
00:40:21,480 --> 00:40:23,220
Katsuo-san.

652
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:28,010
She'll be fine.

653
00:40:28,910 --> 00:40:32,350
Ayu-chan doesn't need to be left
in someone else's hands.

654
00:40:35,490 --> 00:40:37,650
She's a strong individual...

655
00:40:38,500 --> 00:40:40,570
stronger than either of us.

656
00:40:44,700 --> 00:40:46,400
You're absolutely right.

657
00:40:49,510 --> 00:40:51,530
Senpai.

658
00:40:51,530 --> 00:40:54,000
- Cheers.
- Hey.

659
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:56,580
You're not trying to console me, are you?

660
00:40:56,580 --> 00:40:58,120
We're just exchanging glasses, that's all.

661
00:40:58,120 --> 00:41:00,990
I don't think so, but if you insist.

662
00:41:00,990 --> 00:41:04,310
- Here, cheers.
- Cheers!

663
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:08,920
♫ And we can no longer accept each other ♫

664
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:11,770
♫ Ridiculously, we are ♫

665
00:41:11,770 --> 00:41:14,530
It sure is pouring out there.

666
00:41:14,530 --> 00:41:15,640
It sure is.

667
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:20,240
I'm making deliveries,
but feel free to stay until the rain lets up.

668
00:41:20,240 --> 00:41:22,560
Just lock up and put the key
in our mailbox when you leave.

669
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:24,550
Really? Thank you so much.

670
00:41:24,550 --> 00:41:27,180
- Here's the key.
- Okay.

671
00:41:27,180 --> 00:41:30,120
We also have water in the fridge,
so take as much as you need.

672
00:41:30,120 --> 00:41:31,550
- Much appreciated.
- My pleasure.

673
00:41:31,550 --> 00:41:34,210
- Thank you.
- Just remember to leave the key.

674
00:41:36,790 --> 00:41:38,920
♫ What we lacked ♫

675
00:41:38,920 --> 00:41:41,580
He's a good guy.
♫ Wasn't ideals ♫

676
00:41:41,580 --> 00:41:46,320
♫ Notice the warm honesty ♫

677
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:48,920
I feel defeated for some reason.

678
00:41:53,970 --> 00:41:57,090
You don't need to force yourself to move on.

679
00:41:59,990 --> 00:42:02,680
About Ayumi-san, I mean.

680
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:06,810
I thought being obsessed
with someone was lame, but...

681
00:42:07,550 --> 00:42:10,930
I think it just proves
how serious you were about them.

682
00:42:13,050 --> 00:42:14,980
I suppose you're right.

683
00:42:14,980 --> 00:42:18,030
Honestly, I'm a bit jealous.

684
00:42:18,030 --> 00:42:19,380
About what?

685
00:42:19,380 --> 00:42:21,750
You're so stupidly devoted
to someone. It's admirable.

686
00:42:21,750 --> 00:42:24,410
Hey, don't call me stupid.

687
00:42:24,410 --> 00:42:26,030
I'll leave the locking up to you.

688
00:42:26,030 --> 00:42:27,870
What?

689
00:42:27,870 --> 00:42:31,910
- Leaving already?
- I don't want to deal with you getting any drunker.

690
00:42:31,910 --> 00:42:33,590
What's that supposed to mean?

691
00:42:33,590 --> 00:42:36,690
- See you tomorrow.
- Hey...

692
00:42:43,540 --> 00:42:45,320
Minato?

693
00:42:47,380 --> 00:42:49,040
Ko-chan?

694
00:42:51,520 --> 00:42:53,510
Oh, man...

695
00:42:53,510 --> 00:42:55,370
I need water.

696
00:42:55,370 --> 00:42:56,860
Oh, no.

697
00:42:57,590 --> 00:43:05,450
♫ The invisible colors must be yourself ♫

698
00:43:06,400 --> 00:43:10,590
[Minato-san]

699
00:44:08,520 --> 00:44:10,760
All good.

700
00:44:17,850 --> 00:44:19,890
Katsuo-san?

701
00:44:21,290 --> 00:44:23,830
- Ayumi?
- Why?

702
00:44:24,450 --> 00:44:26,040
- What?
- Oh...

703
00:44:26,920 --> 00:44:28,640
Oh, it's you, Ayumi.

704
00:44:28,640 --> 00:44:30,470
What are you doing here?

705
00:44:30,470 --> 00:44:36,670
I just happened... to meet Minato-kun,

706
00:44:36,670 --> 00:44:38,650
and we were drinking together.

707
00:44:39,700 --> 00:44:41,250
Sorry, that's overstepping, right?

708
00:44:41,250 --> 00:44:44,730
But I promise it really was a coincidence.

709
00:44:51,120 --> 00:44:53,630
Where is Minato-san now?

710
00:44:53,630 --> 00:44:57,140
Now? He left earlier to make some deliveries.

711
00:44:57,140 --> 00:44:59,110
"Deliveries"?

712
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:04,750
I see.

713
00:45:06,950 --> 00:45:10,150
So that really was Minato-san.

714
00:45:11,220 --> 00:45:13,650
I thought I was mistaken.

715
00:45:13,650 --> 00:45:15,080
Ayumi?

716
00:45:15,740 --> 00:45:18,990
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm fine. It's nothing.

717
00:45:18,990 --> 00:45:23,790
What should I do? Maybe I should wait here?

718
00:45:23,790 --> 00:45:25,650
Do you have the keys?

719
00:45:25,650 --> 00:45:28,900
- Yes.
- Actually, never mind.

720
00:45:28,900 --> 00:45:32,880
He'd be weirded out to see me waiting here, right?

721
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:34,500
- I'm leaving.
- Ayumi.

722
00:45:34,500 --> 00:45:36,140
I'll wait for him at home.

723
00:45:36,140 --> 00:45:37,890
This doesn't bother me.

724
00:45:37,890 --> 00:45:40,080
It doesn't bother me at all.

725
00:45:41,210 --> 00:45:43,040
Gosh.

726
00:45:44,560 --> 00:45:46,100
Ayumi?

727
00:45:47,810 --> 00:45:49,340
Ayumi.

728
00:45:50,060 --> 00:45:51,640
What?

729
00:45:52,700 --> 00:45:54,230
Are you okay?

730
00:45:56,070 --> 00:45:58,690
Yes, I'm fine.

731
00:46:04,040 --> 00:46:10,660
Even though I wouldn't know when to return to,

732
00:46:10,660 --> 00:46:12,780
I'd still go back in time.

733
00:46:14,890 --> 00:46:17,790
I'd go to see Ayumi all over again.

734
00:46:17,790 --> 00:46:19,280
[Preview]

735
00:46:19,280 --> 00:46:20,590
Not enough color.
[Katsuo's older brother makes an appearance?]

736
00:46:20,590 --> 00:46:21,580
This is my older brother.
[Katsuo's older brother makes an appearance?]

737
00:46:21,580 --> 00:46:22,930
That's hot!

738
00:46:22,930 --> 00:46:24,340
Katsuo-san cried his eyes out?

739
00:46:24,340 --> 00:46:26,020
Oh, Katsuo-san!
[The fossil man is faced with a crisis!]

740
00:46:26,020 --> 00:46:27,240
What a coincidence.
[The fossil man is faced with a crisis!]

741
00:46:27,240 --> 00:46:29,340
Minato-san, I don't want you to go.
[This drama is fiction.]
